api_response = {
    "status": "success",
    "data": {
        "user_profile": {
            "account_id": 9845,
            "credentials": {
                "username": "qa_automation_lead"
            }
        }
    }
}
try:
    # Deep nested extraction
    username = api_response["data"]["user_profile"]["credentials"]["username"]
    print(f"Extracted User: {username}")
except KeyError as e:
    # Fallback assignment handles missing keys gracefully
    username = "Guest_User"
    print(f"Key missing, falling back to default: {e}")
'''Direct bracket lookups dict[key] are fast but hazardous. If any nested layer is missing, Python throws a KeyError. In automation suites, wrapping this assertion in a try-except block keeps the execution pipeline running cleanly.'''
